---
/*
  Translatable prose block. The default slot holds the English text; the
  `ar` slot holds the Arabic translation. Both render to HTML; CSS shows the
  one matching <html data-lang> (set by the language toggle). Code blocks,
  diagrams and Go terms stay outside <Tr> so they remain English/LTR.

  Usage in MDX:
    <Tr>
    English explanation with **markdown** and `code`.
    <Fragment slot="ar">
    الشرح بالعربية مع `code`.
    </Fragment>
    </Tr>
*/
---
<div class="tr">
  <div class="tr-en"><slot /></div>
  <div class="tr-ar" lang="ar" dir="rtl"><slot name="ar" /></div>
</div>
